As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]], there were 1,102 people residing in the community. The racial makeup of the city was 97.47% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 0.24% [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]], 1.93% two or more races, and 0.60% Black or African American.<ref name=":2">{{Cite web |title=Annville, KY |url=https://worldpopulationreview.com/us-cities/annville-ky-population |access-date=August 1, 2022 |website=World Population Review}}</ref>

The median income for a household in the city was $37,957.  About 26.32% of the population were below the [[poverty line]].<ref name=":2" />

The mean cost for a housing unit was $100,100 while the average rent was $664.<ref name=":2" />

